      <h1>Constituent Institutions</h1>
      <p>SIMATS was formerly known as Saveetha University, the name has been changed to Saveetha Institute of Medical and Technical Sciences (Deemed to be University) with effect from 30th Nov. 2017 as per the University Grants Commission Letter No.F.5-2017(CPP.I/DU) dated 29th November 2017 and compliance submitted to UGC in our Ref.No, SU/UGC/1971/A1/2017, dated 30.11.2017.</p>

      <h2>CHANCELLOR</h2>
      <p>Dr. N.M.Veeraiyan was born on 15-11-1947 in Nalligowandanoor, Erode District, and had schooling at Kavandapadi. <article>He is an alumnus of Madras Medical College, one of the premier Institutions of this country. He graduated in Dentistry in 1970. A renowned dental surgeon, Dr. Veeraiyan established a 100 bedded multi-specialty hospital in 1977 and also a School of Nursing for Diploma course, the first of its kind in Erode. </p>
